.TH "__hvc_resize" 9 "__hvc_resize" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__hvc_resize \- Update terminal window size information.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __hvc_resize
.BI "(struct hvc_struct *hp "  ","
.BI "struct winsize ws "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hp" 12
HVC console pointer
.IP "ws" 12
Terminal window size structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Stores the specified window size information in the hvc structure of \fIhp\fP.
The function schedule the tty resize update.

Locking:     Locking free; the function MUST be called holding hp->lock
